Bug Report: WhatsApp Application

Issue: Unable to send messages

Severity: High

Description: Users are unable to send messages in the WhatsApp application. When attempting to send a message, the app displays an error message stating that the message could not be sent. However, the message does not contain any prohibited content or violate any of the app's policies.

Steps to Reproduce:

Open WhatsApp application.
Navigate to a chat.
Type a message and click on the send button.
The app displays an error message stating that the message could not be sent.
Expected Result: The message should be sent successfully to the recipient.

Actual Result: The app displays an error message and the message cannot be sent.

Additional Information:

This issue occurs with all messages, regardless of the recipient or message content.
The issue is not present when sending messages through other messaging apps.
Other types of files, such as images and documents, can be sent successfully.
This issue is affecting both Android and iOS versions of the WhatsApp application.
Workaround: There is currently no known workaround for this issue.

Impact: This issue is impacting users' ability to effectively communicate and share information through the app. It is a critical issue and requires immediate attention.

Reproducibility: The issue is reproducible on multiple devices and across different network connections.

Environment:

WhatsApp version: Latest version on both Android and iOS
Device: Various Android and iOS devices
Operating System: Android 11 and iOS 14.5.1
Attachments: Screenshots of error message and message details.

Recommendation: The WhatsApp development team should investigate and resolve this issue as soon as possible to prevent further impact on users' ability to communicate effectively.
